<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="582" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="30.[1389,2598,836,1893]" pageId="30" pageNumber="582">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1391,1749,1706,1735]" pageId="30" pageNumber="582">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List (under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wagner" authorityYear="1845" box="[1392,1532,1750,1775]" class="Mammalia" family="Echimyidae" genus="Isothrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="30" pageNumber="582" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bistriata">I. bistriata</taxonomicName>
). Additional studies on distribution, habitat, abundance, ecology, and conservation threats to the Orinoco Brush-tailed Rat are needed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
